      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey... i need to tell someone this because i feel like i'm going crazy. i was looking at a chipped blue coffee mug this morning, just a random thing, but for a split second i saw the reflection of a headline in the ceramic surface. it said \"unprecedented storm surge hits coast\" and then i blinked and it was just a mug again. but then an hour later the news actually reported exactly that. does that even happen? i'm seeing these little flashes in objects and it's getting weird.",
